      • testTicket567

        public void testTicket567()
                   throws org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException,
                          org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                          org.openrdf.query.UpdateExecutionException
        Unit test for 
         DROP ALL;
 INSERT DATA {
 GRAPH  {
    .
    .
 }};
 ADD SILENT GRAPH  TO GRAPH  ;
 DROP SILENT GRAPH   ;
        The IV cache was not not being propagated correctly with the result that we were seeing mock IVs for "one" and "two". The UPDATE would work correctly the 2nd time since the URIs had been entered into the dictionary by then.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        org.openrdf.query.UpdateExecutionException
        See Also:
        Failure to set cached value on IV results in incorrect behavior for complex UPDATE operation

      • testTicket571

        public void testTicket571()
                   throws org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException,
                          org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                          org.openrdf.query.UpdateExecutionException,
                          org.openrdf.query.QueryEvaluationException
        In the ticket, the source file contains the following triples. In this test, those are triples are written into the graph using INSERT DATA rather than LOAD so this test can be self-contained. 
         _:bnode  2 .
 _:bnode a  .
   2 .
        Load into graphA: 
         PREFIX graphA:  
 PREFIX tempGraph:  
 DROP SILENT GRAPH tempGraph: ;
 DROP SILENT GRAPH graphA: ;
 INSERT DATA {
 GRAPH graphA: {
   _:bnode  2 . 
   _:bnode a  . 
     2 . 
 }}
        Verify that all three triples are in graphA: 
         PREFIX graphA:  
 PREFIX tempGraph:  
 SELECT * WHERE { GRAPH graphA: { ?s ?p ?v . } }
        Now delete some triples from graphA while inserting the deleted triples into tempGraph: 
         PREFIX graphA:  
 PREFIX tempGraph:  
 DROP SILENT GRAPH tempGraph: ;
 DELETE { GRAPH graphA:    { ?s ?p ?v . } }
 INSERT { GRAPH tempGraph: { ?s ?p ?v . } }
 WHERE { GRAPH graphA: { 
     ?s a  .
     ?s ?p ?v . } }
        The result should be that the combination of tempGraph and graphA should have the exact same number of triples that we started with. But now notice that graphA has 0 triples: 
         PREFIX graphA:  
 PREFIX tempGraph:  
 SELECT * WHERE { GRAPH graphA: { ?s ?p ?v . } }
        However, tempGraph has only 2 triples: 
         PREFIX graphA:  
 PREFIX tempGraph:  
 SELECT * WHERE { GRAPH tempGraph: { ?s ?p ?v . } }
        so one triple is missing: 
           2 .
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.QueryEvaluationException
        org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        org.openrdf.query.UpdateExecutionException

      • testUnicodeCleanAndRegex

        public void testUnicodeCleanAndRegex()
                              throws Exception
        This test is based on a forum post. This post provided an example of an issue with Unicode case-folding in the REGEX operator and a means to encode the Unicode characters to avoid doubt about which characters were transmitted and receieved.
        Throws:
        Exception
        See Also:
        Forum post on the REGEX Unicode case-folding issue, SPARQL REGEX operator does not perform case-folding correctly for Unicode data
